description: Commit message conventions; no Cursor branding in commits
alwaysApply: true
---

# Commit Messages

- Write clear, concise commit messages that describe the change.
- Do **not** mention Cursor (or similar IDE branding) anywhere in the commit subject or body.
- Do not append tool or product names to commits unless they are technically relevant (e.g. "Upgrade Maven plugin").
- When the user asks to commit each file separately: one `git add` + one `git commit` per file, then push.
